Citation.sTitle: Solid and Liquid Phase Equilibria in Mixtures of 1,8-Cineole with Phenol, Cyclohexanol, and an n-Alkanol
Citation.sAbstract: Solid-liquid phase diagrams have been constructed for 1,8-cineole with phenol or cyclohexanol or an n-alkanol. Solid addition compounds with the empirical formulas C10H18O*C6H5OH and C10H18O*C6H11OH were formed. Compound formation is attributed to hydrogen bonding. No solid addition compounds form in (1,8-cineole + methanol, + ethanol, + 1-propanol, or + 1-butanol).
